Netcare Secures a Wage Agreement With Solidarity Union, Workers Group Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-03-15T08:31:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/netcare-secures-a-wage-agreement-with-solidarity-union-workers-group-says.html
  Netcare Ltd. (NTC)  has secured a wage
agreement with  South Africa ’s Solidarity labor union, the
workers’ organization said in an e-mailed statement today.  The parties agreed a wage deal of 7.75 percent for all
nursing, administrative and support staff, while in addition,
employees in the minimum salary group will receive a 9 percent
wage increase, Solidarity said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  